text:
Svenja Engelhardt (born April 20, 1988 in Heidelberg) is a German volleyball and beach volleyball player. She teamed with Britta Büthe's to win a bronze medal at the 2006 FIVB Beach Volleyball U19 World Championships. She played at the 2013 FIVB World Grand Prix.
She played for University of the Pacific's women's volleyball team. She played for VS Post Schwechat, Allianz MTV Stuttgart, and VC Offenburg.
